properties.areaDesc: Big Island Southeast Waters; Alenuihaha Channel; Big Island Windward Waters
properties.headline: Gale Warning issued February 10 at 9:19AM HST until February 10 at 6:00PM HST by NWS Honolulu HI
properties.description:
* WHAT...West to northwest winds 25 to 35 kt with stronger gusts
and seas 9 to 14 feet.

* WHERE...Alenuihaha Channel, Big Island Windward Waters and Big
Island Southeast Waters.

* WHEN...Until 6 PM HST this evening.

* IMPACTS...Conditions will be hazardous to small craft.
properties.instruction:
A Gale Warning means winds of 34 to 47 knots are imminent or
occurring. Operating a vessel in gale conditions requires
experience and properly equipped vessels. It is highly
recommended that mariners without the proper experience seek safe
harbor prior to the onset of gale conditions.

NWSheadline: GALE WARNING IN EFFECT UNTIL 6 PM HST THIS EVENING
